        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <head>No. 107.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Lord <persName type="to">Tenterden</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                        Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 12,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[From British Blue Book “North America,” No. 10, (1872,) p.
                            2.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: Sir Roundell Palmer having consented,
                            at the request of Her Majesty’s Government, to attend the meeting of the
                            Tribunal of Arbitration on the 15th instant as Her Majesty’s Counsel, I
                            have to instruct you to be guided by his advice in all your
                            proceedings.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
